The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Feb. 8: The government today decided to exempt sugar meant for exports from levy obligation, to make the commodity more attractive. The government decided to offer incentives to sugar exports as global prices are low, making its export uneconomic. The global prices are hovering around $335 per tonne. 

 New Delhi, Feb. 8: India and Greece are likely to sign agreements on avoidance of double taxation and investment protection, Greek minister of economy and finance George Alogoskoufis said after meeting P. Chidambaram. There are, however, some legal issues to be sorted out. It is more important to establish close relations with India, Alogoskoufis said at a Ficci meeting. 

 Mumbai, Feb. 8: Larsen and Toubro (L amp;T) has entered into a memorandum of understanding with Boeing to explore business opportunities in Indias defence sector. The signing ceremony took place at the Aero -India aerospace show in Bangalore.

 New York, Feb. 8: Verizon Communications is applying for a long-distance operating licence in India that will allow it to compete with AT amp;T and other telecom firms offering phone and internet services to multinational firms. 

 Bangalore, Feb. 8: Caritor has entered into a definitive agreement with Keane Inc to acquire it for $854 million in an all-cash deal.




